        .form-check.sa-checkbox
          %input#blankCheckbox-2.form-check-input{"aria-label" => "...", :type => "checkbox", :value => "option1"}/
          %label.form-check-label{:for => "blankCheckbox-2"}
            %span.checkbox
        
        .form-check.sa-radio-buttons
          %input#blankRadio2-1.form-check-input{"aria-label" => "...", :name => "blankRadio", :type => "radio", :value => "option1"}/
          %label.form-check-label.radio-button{:for => "blankRadio2-1"}
            %span



  .col-sm-12
    %hr/
    %h3 Toggle Switches
    %p
      Toggle Switches are based on Checkboxes or Radios. Each has a specific purpose and each is written slighly differently. 
    .card.card-sard
      .card-header Toggle Switches
      .card-body
        .row  
          .col-sm-6
            .sa-toggle-switch
              %input#advanced_when_toggle{type: 'checkbox', name: 'advanced_when', class: 'advanced_when'}
              %label{:for => "advanced_when_toggle"} 
                %span.slider .sa-toggle-switch
          .col-sm-6
            .sa-toggle-switch-right
              %input#advanced_when_toggle_right{type: 'checkbox', name: 'advanced_when', class: 'advanced_when'}
              %label{:for => "advanced_when_toggle_right"} 
                %span.slider .sa-toggle-switch-right
      .card-body
        %p 
          %code .sa-toggle-switch 
          is a form of checkbox. 
          %br/
          They can be arranged either left (default) or right by using the class of
          %code .sa-toggle-switch-right
          instead.


    .card.card-sard
      .card-header Radio Toggles
      .card-body
        .row
          .col-sm-6
            .sa-radio-toggle
              %input#sa-radio-toggle-one{:checked => "checked", :name => "user", :type => "radio", :value => "false"}/
              %label{:for => "sa-radio-toggle-one"}
                %span.radio Top
            .sa-radio-toggle
              %input#sa-radio-toggle-two{:name => "user", :type => "radio", :value => "true"}/
              %label{:for => "sa-radio-toggle-two"}
                %span.radio Bottom
          .col-sm-6
            .sa-radio-toggle-right
              %input#sa-radio-toggle-three{:checked => "checked", :name => "user2", :type => "radio", :value => "false"}/
              %label{:for => "sa-radio-toggle-three"}
                %span.radio Top
            .sa-radio-toggle-right
              %input#sa-radio-toggle-four{:name => "user2", :type => "radio", :value => "true"}/
              %label{:for => "sa-radio-toggle-four"}
                %span.radio Bottom
      .card-body
        %p 
          %code .sa-radio-toggle 
          is a set of radio buttons, when one is selected, the other is de-selected. 
          %br/
          They can be arranged either left (default) or right by using the class of
          %code .sa-radio-toggle-right
          instead.


    .card.card-sard
      .card-header Toggle Check
      .card-body
        .row
          .col-sm-6
            .sa-toggle-check
              %label
                %input.toggle-check-input{:type => "checkbox", id: "own_cpd_record", class: "have_own_cpd", name: "own_cpd_record", value: "true", checked: "checked"}/
                %span.toggle-check-text
          .col-sm-6
            .sa-toggle-check-right
              %label
                %input.toggle-check-input{:type => "checkbox", id: "own_cpd_record", class: "have_own_cpd", name: "own_cpd_record", value: "true", checked: "checked"}/
                %span.toggle-check-text
      .card-body
        %p 
          %code .sa-toggle-check 
          is a single checkbox, with a YES / NO Statement.
          %br/
          They can be arranged either left (default) or right by using the class of
          %code .sa-toggle-check-right
          instead.

        